SENATE BILL No. 164
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
agriculture and animals.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 15-11-2-10 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
2 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
3 1, 2026]: Sec. 10. (a) The department shall conduct a formal study
4 in collaboration with the following persons to evaluate the
5 feasibility of establishing community or urban microfarm zones
6 statewide:
7 (1) The Indiana department of health.
8 (2) The Purdue University cooperative extension service.
9 (3) Any local government.
10 (4) Any community based organization.
11 (b) The study conducted under subsection (a) must include the
12 following:
13 (1) An inventory of suitable vacant or underutilized parcels
14 for community agriculture.
15 (2) Identification of zoning templates and best practices for
16 community or urban microfarm management.
17 (3) An evaluation of how community or urban microfarms
2026 IN 164—LS 6716/DI 148

2
1 support food access, nutrition education, and community
2 engagement.
3 (4) Opportunities for partnerships with the Purdue University
4 cooperative extension service, local health departments,
5 health care providers, and educational institutions.
6 (c) Not later than July 1, 2027, the department shall submit a
7 report to the general assembly, in an electronic format under
8 IC 5-14-6, with the following information:
9 (1) The findings regarding subsection (b)(1) through (b)(4).
10 (2) A specific finding as to:
11 (A) whether and how community or urban microfarm
12 zones could work in Indiana; and
13 (B) what options are available for future pilot programs or
14 technical assistance.
15 (3) A recommendation for:
16 (A) standards to ensure safety and compatibility; and
17 (B) future legislation to implement community or urban
18 microfarm zones.
